{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χιών</b>, όνος, ἡ: <br /> (see. entry near the end):— <b>snow,</b> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] mostly of <b>fallen snow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.7, 22.152; ὡς δὲ χ. κατατήκετ᾽ ἐν.. ὄρεσσιν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.205; ὕπερθε χ. γένετ᾽ ἠΰτε πάχνη 14.476; τὸν Νεῖλον ῥέειν ἀπὸ τηκομένης χιόνος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.22 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ χιόνι πεσούσῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage], compare 4.50; Ἰδαία χ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 564; ἥλιος.. τήκει πετραίαν χιόνα [prev. author] “fragment” 300.5; καί νιν.. χιὼν οὐδαμὰ λείπει 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 830 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of <b>falling snow,</b> ὥς τε νιφάδες χιόνος πίπτωσι θαμειαί thick fall the <b>snow</b>-flakes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.278; χ. πίπτουσα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.31; κατένειψε χιόνι τὴν Θρᾴκην 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 138; ὅταν βορέας χιόνα χέῃ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 329, compare “Ba.” 662; ἐπιπίπτει χ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.4.11; χιόνες πολλαὶ γίνονται 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Signis Tempestatum” 24: [χ.] σφοδρὰ καὶ ἀθρόα καταφερομένη νιφετὸς ὠνόμασται 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Mundo” 394a36. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>snow-water, 'ice-coldwater,</b> Θρῄκην χιόνι.. κατάρρυτον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 215; χ. ποταμία [prev. author] “Tr.” 1067 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; used to cool wine, εἰ χιών ἐστ᾽ ὠνία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Euthycles Comicus 1; οἶνον πιεῖν.. χιόνι μεμιγμένον 5th c.BC: Strattis Comicus 57; χιόνα πίνειν 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 141.10; τοῦ θέρους χιόνα.. ζητεῖς Χ. “Mem.” 2.1.30; ἡδὺ θέρους.. χιὼν ποτόν “Anthologia Graeca” 5.168 (1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: rare in <i>plural</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Mundo” 394a16 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]. [ῐ by nature, ῑ <i>Epic dialect</i> for the sake of meter] (Cf. Sanskrit <i>himás</i> 'cold, winter', Latin <i>hiems,</i> Avest. <b>zyam-</b> 'winter', etc.)","strongNumber":"G5510","accentedUnicode":"χιών","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5494","matchingForm":"χειμών","stepTransliteration":"cheimōn","gloss":"winter","_zh_tw_Gloss":"冬天","_es_Gloss":"invierno","_zh_Gloss":"冬天"}],"shortDef":"snow","mediumDef":"<b>snow,</b> <ref='Mat.28.3'>Mt. 28:3</ref>; <ref='Rev.1.14'>Rev. 1:14</ref>*","stepGloss":"snow","stepTransliteration":"chiōn","count":3,"_es_Definition":"nieve","_zh_tw_Definition":"雪","_zh_Definition":"雪","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"tuyết","_zh_tw_Gloss":"雪","_es_Gloss":"nieve","_zh_Gloss":"雪"}]}